1.title: The Masterpiece
1.plot: Paul pulls no punches in trying to get his hands on the ultimate mansion, meanwhile, Kenny struggles to prove the naysayers wrong by trying to procure a photo shoot location for a celebrity client, Audrina Patridge.

2.title: House of Horrors
2.plot: Camilla finds herself on a location shoot from hell when a scary movie set becomes a nightmare, and across town in Malibu, Jen is seeing red because of a client who only sees orange.

3.title: You Get What You Give
3.plot: Paul may have bitten off more than he can chew with a charity fundraiser and when Marisa's old flame comes to town for a photo shoot, Camilla and Marisa butt heads when Marisa lets him get away with too much.

4.title: Double Booked
4.plot: When two clients vie for the same mansion, Jen & Camilla must battle it out to find a solution, and when Paul's stress level gets out of hand, Marisa and Kenny embark on a secret mission.

5.title: A Not-So Friendly Competition
5.plot: Kenny is in hot water with Jen when everything falls apart on the Nadia Forde music video shoot, and Paul's company is threatened by some very close competition.

6.title: In the Doghouse
6.plot: Paul & Marisa scour Malibu for a picky heiress, and if meeting their client's many demands wasn't enough, the client's dog has the final say on mansion approval, meanwhile, Camilla comes under fire for one of Kenny's mistakes.

7.title: Raising the Black Dahlia
7.plot: When Paul mixes business and friendship with an eccentric friend, he finds their relationship and his own sanity is put to the test, and Carey & Camilla take a walk on the dark side when it turns out that Carey's clients are hoping to raise the dead.

8.title: Are You Lion to Me?
8.plot: Kenny puts his client's shoot in jeopardy when the homeowner is the last to know about a lion on her premises and Paul's relationship with a longtime client gets messy when a film shoot leaves the location trashed.

imdb.plot outline: When Hollywood's hot celebrities, production companies and fashion photographers need exclusive access to a luxurious mansion for work or play, there's one man they call: Paul Kim. Paul started his Image Locations business with three maxed out credit cards and a single cell phone. It wasn't long before Image Locations grew into one of the leading property rental companies in America. Whether it's a massive and modern location for a couture fashion shoot, a sprawling yard for a million dollar wedding reception, or a three month party-pad for a wealthy heiress, Image Locations handles it all. Navigating the turbulent world of the rich and famous is tricky and alive with drama, so Paul has assembled a team of passionate and loyal experts to deal with the outlandish requests, eccentric characters and million dollar deals they come face to face with every day. In this high stakes game, disasters loom and tempers will flare, but it's all in a day's work for the Mansion Hunters.
